0.Positioning (Rapid traverse):

1.Linear interpolation (Cutting feed):

IP - For an absolute command, the coordinates of an end point, and for an incremental command, the distance the tool moves.

10.9.Programmable switching of diameter/radiu:
G10.9 IP_; 
IP : Address and command value of an specified axis subject to diameter/radius specification switching 
Specify 0 or 1 as the command value. 
0: Radius specification 
1: Diameter specification 

Specify G10.9 in a single block specifying no other codes. 
After an axis address, specify a command value without using the decimal point.

34.Variable lead threading:
G34 IP_ F_ K_ Q_; 
IP - End point 
F - Lead in longitudinal axis direction at the start point 
K - Increment and decrement of lead per spindle revolution 
Q - Shift amount of starting angle of thread cutting

35.Circular threading CW:
G35 X_ Z_ <I_ K_ R_> F_ Q_; 
G35 - Clockwise circular threading command 
X, Z - Specify the arc end point (in the same way as for G02, G03) 
I, K - Specify the arc center relative to the start point, using relative coordinates (in the same way as for G02, G03) 
R - Specify the arc radius 
F - Specify the lead in the direction of the major axis 
Q - Specify the shift of the threading start angle

36.Circular threading CCW:
G36 X_ Z_ <I_ K_ R_> F_ Q_; 
G36 - Counterclockwise circular threading command 
X, Z - Specify the arc end point (in the same way as for G02, G03) 
I, K - Specify the arc center relative to the start point, using relative coordinates (in the same way as for G02, G03) 
R - Specify the arc radius 
F - Specify the lead in the direction of the major axis 
Q - Specify the shift of the threading start angle

43.4.Tool center point control TCP (type 1):
G43.4 IP_ α_ β_ H_ ; Starts tool center point control (type 1). 
IP_ α_ β_ ; 
IP - In the case of an absolute programming, the coordinate value of the end point of the tool tip movement In the case of an incremental programming, the amount of the tool tip movement 
α, β - In the case of an absolute programming, the coordinate value of the end point of the rotary axes In the case of an incremental programming, the amount of the rotary axis movement 
H - Tool offset number

43.5.Tool center point control TCP (type 2):
G43.5 IP_ H_ Q_ ; Starts tool center point control (type 2). 
IP_ I_ J_ K_ ; 
IP - In the case of an absolute programming, the coordinate value of the end point of the tool tip movement In the case of an incremental programming, the amount of the tool tip movement 
I, J, K - Tool axis direction at the block end point as seen from the programming coordinate system 
H - Tool offset number 
Q  Inclination angle of the tool (in degrees)

73.Chip Break Drilling Cycle:
Chip break drilling with retraction to the startplane G98 or the withdrawal plane G99 
G98(G99) G73 X_ Y_ Z_ (R)_ P_ Q_ F_ K_ 
G98(G99) - Return to starting plane 
X,Y - Hole position 
Z - Absolute (incremental) drilling depth 
R - Absolute (with G91 incremental) value of the withdrawal plane 
P[msec] - Dwell at the hole bottom P1000 = 1 sec 
F -  Feedrate 
Q - Cutting division - infeed per cut 
K - Number of repetitions

74.Left-handed tapping cycle:
With this cycle left threads can be produced. The cycle G74 works like G84 but with reversed turning directions. 
G98(G99) - G74 X_ Y_ Z_ (R)_ F_ P_ K_ 
G98(G99) - Return to starting plane 
X,Y - Hole position 
Z - Absolute (incremental) tapping depth 
R - Absolute (with G91 incremental) value of the withdrawal plane 
F - Feedrate with G94, Thread pitch with G95 
P[msec] - Dwell at the hole bottom P1000 = 1 sec 
F -  Feedrate 
K - Number of repetitions

83.Peck drilling cycle:
G98(G99) G83 X... Y... Z... (R)... P... Q... F... K... 

The tool dips into the work piece for the infeed Q, drives back to the withdrawal plane, to break the chips and remove it from the hole, traverses with rapid speed until 0,5 mm over the previous drilling depth, dips in again for the infeed Q etc. until end depth is reached and retracts with rapid feed. 

G98(G99) - G81 X_ Y_ Z_ (R)_ F_ P_ K_ 
G98(G99) - Retraction to start plane 
X,Y - Hole position 
Z - Absolute (incremental) drilling depth 
R - Absolute (with G91 incremental) value of the withdrawal plane 
P[msec] - Dwell at the hole bottom P1000 = 1 sec 
F - Feed 
Q - Cutting division - infeed per cut 
K - Number of repetitions

84.Tapping cycle:
The tool moves turning clockwise with programmed feed into the workpiece down to drilling depth Z, dwells (P), switches to counterclockwise turning and retracts with feed.

X,Y - Hole position 
Z - Absolute (incremental) tapping depth 
R - Absolute (with G91 incremental) value of the withdrawal plane 
F - Feedrate with G94, Thread pitch with G95 
P[msec] - Dwell at the hole bottom P1000 = 1 sec 
F -  Feedrate 
K - Number of repetitions
